I am a bit confused on how the residual is computed in NodalEqualValueConstraint
so basically, we get the residual for the LM variable, and define it as



      moose/framework/src/kernels/NodalEqualValueConstraint.C


        Lines 34 to 43
      in
      40ea18c







           void 




           NodalEqualValueConstraint::computeResidual() 




           { 




             prepareVectorTag(_assembly, _var.number()); 









             for (unsigned int k = 0; k < _value.size(); k++) 




               _local_re(k) = (*_value[k])[0] - (*_value[k])[1]; 









             assignTaggedLocalResidual(); 




           } 





now the _value holds the constrained variable value, the way it is indexed in that for loop doesn't make sense to me.
shouldnt it be  (*_value[0])[0] - (*_value[1])[0] since it's a nodal variable and only the first index that holds the variable values?
also, the value changes every time the the loop itterates, so not sure how does this work.
thanks again in advance!

